==={{transliteration|ja|Kuge-mono}}===
{{transliteration|ja|Kuge-mono}} are tales of the aristocracy.{{sfnm|1a1=Ichiko|1y=1983|1p=498}}<!-- Not technically verified in the source, but a literal translation of the word the source uses. --> They mark a continuation of the earlier {{transliteration|ja|monogatari}} literature,{{sfnm|1a1=Ichiko|1y=1983|1p=498}} and are noted for the influence of ''[[The Tale of Genji]]''.{{sfnm|1a1=Ichiko|1y=1983|1p=498}} Many of them are rewritten or abridged versions of earlier works.{{sfnm|1a1=Ichiko|1y=1983|1p=498}} Among the romantic works in this sub-genre are {{nihongo||忍音物語|[[Shinobine Monogatari]]}} and {{nihongo||若草物語|[[Wakakusa Monogatari]]}},{{sfnm|1a1=Ichiko|1y=1983|1p=498}} and most end sadly with the characters cutting themselves off from society<!-- entering Buddhist orders? --> ({{nihongo||悲恋遁世|hiren tonsei}}).{{sfnm|1a1=Ichiko|1y=1983|1p=498}}
